edu.iit.ir.simpledm.preprocess
Class Preprocessor

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--edu.iit.ir.simpledm.preprocess.Preprocessor
public class Preprocessor
extends java.lang.Object

Contains preprocessing services and boolean values of each service indicating if the preprocessing is selected by a user or not. PreprocessPanel.java calls this class to set the selected options.
There are several preprocessing services.

  • Removes Over-fitting in a SampleSet.
  • Replaces the missing values. (Empty for version 1.1)
  • Transforms from categorical attributes to continuous or continuous to categorical(discretization).
  • Normalizes the continuous values.(Z-score function is empty for version 1.1)


Each preprocessing service is performed by one function.

However, void preprocess(SampleSet, boolean) performs every selected preprocesssing. This function is called by Model.java before building a model with the preprocessed SampleSet.

Method Detail

preprocess

public SampleSet preprocess(SampleSet samples,
                            boolean trainData)
Performs the selected preprocessing among 'removing over-fitting', 'replacing missing values', 'transformation' and 'normalization' on the given SampleSet. The order of calling selected function is 'removeOverFit(SampleSet)', 'replaceMissingValues(SampleSet)', 'transformToCategorical(SampleSet)' or 'transformToContinuous(SampleSet)' 'normalizeMinmax(SampleSet)'.

Parameters:
samples - - SampleSet.
trainData - - boolean which is true if the SampleSet is training data.
